#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code postfix ko prefix me convert karne ke liye stack of strings use karta hai.

1. Expression ko left se right traverse karte hain.
2. Agar operand mile, to usse string bana ke stack me push kar do.
3. Agar operator mile, to stack se top ke 2 operands pop karo:
   - first pop = first operand
   - second pop = second operand
4. Prefix expression banane ka rule:
   operator + second + first
   (kyuki postfix me order operand operand operator hota hai,
    aur prefix me operator operand operand hota hai)
5. Naya string bana ke stack me push kar do.
6. End me stack ka top hi final prefix expression hoga.

Main idea:
Postfix: operand operand operator
Prefix: operator operand operand
Isliye operator milte hi 2 operands ko nikaal ke unka order change karke new string bana dete hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {

    public boolean isOperator(Character a){
        if((a == '+') || (a == '-') || (a == '*') || (a == '/')){
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }

    public String postToPre(String postfix) {
        // Your code goes here
        int n = postfix.length();
        int i = 0;
        ArrayDeque<String> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();

        while(i < n){
            char ch = postfix.charAt(i);

            //ch is an operator: operator second first
            if(isOperator(ch)){
                String first = stack.pop();
                String second = stack.pop();
                String temp = ch + second + first;
                stack.push(temp);
            }
            //if ch is an operand
            else{
                stack.push(Character.toString(ch));
            }
            i++;
        }
        return stack.peek();
    }
}
